WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.240
CHAPTER XVI.

00:09.360 --> 00:15.140
The preparations of the heart in man, and the answer of the tongue, is from the Lord.

00:15.640 --> 00:21.240
All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes, but the Lord weigheth the spirits.

00:22.340 --> 00:27.200
Commit thy works unto the Lord, and thy thoughts shall be established.

00:27.960 --> 00:33.720
The Lord hath made all things for himself, yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.

00:34.760 --> 00:38.420
Every one that is proud in heart is an abomination to the Lord.

00:39.420 --> 00:43.180
Though hand joined in hand, he shall not be unpunished.

00:44.320 --> 00:50.300
By mercy and truth iniquity is purged, and by the fear of the Lord men depart from evil.

00:51.220 --> 00:56.760
When a man's ways please the Lord, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.

00:56.760 --> 01:02.120
Better is a little with righteousness, than great revenues without right.

01:03.480 --> 01:08.400
A man's heart deviseth his way, but the Lord directeth his steps.

01:09.320 --> 01:15.040
A divine sentence is in the lips of the King, his mouth transgresseth not in judgment.

01:15.920 --> 01:22.100
A just weight and balance are the Lord's, all the weights of the bag are his work.

01:22.100 --> 01:29.040
It is an abomination to kings to commit wickedness, for the throne is established by righteousness.

01:30.560 --> 01:35.760
Righteous lips are the delight of kings, and they love him that speaketh right.

01:36.980 --> 01:42.720
The wrath of a king is as messengers of death, but a wise man will pacify it.

01:43.320 --> 01:50.200
In the light of the king's countenance is life, and his favor is as a cloud of the latter rain.

01:50.200 --> 01:57.940
How much better is it to get wisdom than gold, and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver?

01:58.660 --> 02:01.600
The highway of the upright is to depart from evil.

02:02.220 --> 02:05.480
He that keepeth his way, preserveth his soul.

02:06.440 --> 02:12.000
Pride goeth before destruction, and in haughty spirit before a fall.

02:12.800 --> 02:19.780
Better it is to be of a humble spirit with the lowly, than to divide the spoil with the proud.

02:20.860 --> 02:27.960
He that handleeth a matter wisely shall find good, and whoso trusteth in the Lord happy is he.

02:29.140 --> 02:35.120
The wise in heart shall be called prudent, and the sweetness of the lips increaseeth learning.

02:36.660 --> 02:42.880
Understanding is a wellspring of life unto him that hath it, but the instruction of fools is folly.

02:44.020 --> 02:49.020
The heart of the wise teacheth his mouth, and addeth learning to his lips.

02:50.200 --> 02:55.520
Pleasant words are as an honeycomb sweet to the soul and health to the bones.

02:56.640 --> 03:02.720
There is a way that seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.

03:04.060 --> 03:09.540
He that laboreth, laboreth for himself, for his mouth craveth it of him.

03:10.000 --> 03:15.140
An ungodly man diggeth up evil, and in his lips there is a burning fire.

03:15.850 --> 03:21.920
A foward man soweth strife, and a whisperer separateth chief friends.

03:23.060 --> 03:29.240
A violent man enticeth his neighbor, and leadeth him into the way that is not good.

03:29.740 --> 03:35.760
He shutteth his eyes to devise foward things, moving his lips he bringeth evil to pass.

03:36.700 --> 03:41.880
The hoary head is a crown of glory, if it be found in the way of righteousness.

03:42.620 --> 03:46.040
He that is slow to anger is better than the mighty,

03:46.740 --> 03:50.900
and he that ruleth his spirit than he that taketh a city.

03:51.540 --> 03:56.500
The lot is cast into the lap, but the whole disposing thereof is of the Lord.

